Some background data on _Escherichia coli_ O157 infection in Northern Ireland
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Year / Cases
1990 / 1
1991 / 2
1992 / 1
1993 / 2
1994 / 3
1995 / 7
1996 / 14
1997 / 30
1998 / 29
1999 / 54
2000 / 54
2001 / 52
2002 / 28
Outbreaks:
A family cluster (4 cases, ascribed to ham) was reported in 1998.
One outbreak (8 cases) of _E. coli_ O157 infection was reported in a
nursery in 2000.
One outbreak (16 cases) of _E. coli_ O157 infection was reported in a
primary school in 2001.
No outbreaks of _E. coli_ O157 infection were reported in 2002.
--
Dr Steve Berger
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
